What is the projected market size & growth rate of the Power Air Purifying Respirator Market?

Market Analysis and Insights :

Global Power Air Purifying Respirator Market

Data Bridge Market Research analyses that the power air purifying respirator market will witness a CAGR of 9.00% for the forecast period of 2021-2028. Increasing adoption of stringent occupational safety and health standards especially in the developing economies like India and China, growing use of power air purifying respirator by a wide range of end user verticals such as oil and gas, metal fabrication, agriculture, food and beverage, fire services, chemical and others and surge in industrialization especially in the developing countries are the major factors attributable to the growth of the power air purifying respirator market. Therefore, the power air purifying respirator market value, which was USD 4100 million in 2019, will rocket up to USD 4469 million by 2028.

The power air purifying respirator systems are motorized systems that are used to clear and clean the ambient air before it is delivered to the breathing zone. These systems used a blower to pass the contaminated air and therefore remove the contaminants and impurities.

Rise in demand by the various industries coupled with stringent regulations imposed by the government in regards to employees’ health and safety is the root cause fuelling up the market growth rate. Rising industrialization coupled with growth and expansion of various end user verticals such as healthcare, pharmaceutical and food and beverages industries especially in the developing economies will also directly and positively impact the growth rate of the market. Growth in the number of industrial fatalities coupled with surge in the awareness among the workers and employees about these systems will further carve the way for the growth of the market.

However, low penetration rate in the backward areas will pose a major challenge to the growth of the market. Fluctuations in the prices of raw materials will dampen the market growth rate. Complex manufacturing process will further derail the market growth rate. Dearth of skilled professionals in the underdeveloped economies will also impede the market growth rate.

